===Etymology 1===
Compound of {{compound|lang=ja|sort=のび|野|tr1=no|t1=field|火|tr2=hi|t2=fire}}.  The ''hi'' changes to ''bi'' due to {{rendaku|のび}}.

An ancient variant seen in eastern Japan uses the dialectical reading ''nu'' for {{Jpan|野}}.

Use of this kanji {{Jpan|燹}} is rare, and is an example of [[熟字訓#Japanese|jukujikun]].  The standard spelling is {{l|ja|野火}}.

