=====Usage notes=====
Spelled using this kanji {{Jpan|燹}} excludes the "''controlled agricultural burn''" sense found found under the {{l|ja|野火}} spelling.

===Etymology 2===
Compound of {{compound|lang=ja|sort=ほそけ|火|tr1=ho|t1=fire|退く|tr2=soku|t2=to push away, to make distant}}.

The [[kun'yomi]] for {{l|ja|火}} is usually ''hi'', but it can appear as ''ho'' or ''fu'', particularly in older compounds.

The ''soku'' changes to ''soke'' due to [[conjugation]] of the verb.  Grammatically, the stem form ({{l|ja|連用形|tr=''ren'yōkei''}}) ''soki'' would be expected; ''soke'' may indicate either a sound shift over time from a previous ''soki'' conjugation, or that the verb in this compound was originally conjugated into the hypothetical form ({{l|ja|仮定形|tr=''kateikei''}}) ''soke''.

Use of this kanji {{Jpan|燹}} is rare, and is an example of [[熟字訓|jukujikun]].  The more common spelling is {{l|ja|火退}}.

====Noun====
{{ja-noun|k|hira=ほそけ|rom=hosoke}} {{context|rare|lang=ja|sort=ほそけ}}

